<br>
Let me remind you that you will be on a probationary period for a short period of time.  This is in NO way to be a form of harassment, but rather a way for us to evaluate you.  We take great pride in being a guild that works for the common good, vice the success of the individual. <br>
<br>
Secrets to your success will be:<br>
Get involved in Guild activities<br>
Be active on this board, ie. read and reply to messages<br>
Participate in Guild Chat<br>
Be available to guild mates or our alliance Guild, Mystic Entity, when called upon.<br>
Don't be selfish and greedy<br>
Continue the good reputation of Benevolent Order.<br>
<br>
I hope that these criteria are not too overbearing to you.  I understand that folks get involved with guilds for different reasons.  If what I have addressed does not suit your fancy, then perhaps this is not the guild for you.  If you decide during your probationary status that you want to pursue participation with another guild, you certainly have that right.  Be advised that we as a Guild also have the right to remove you from B.O. if we deem necessary ( very unlikely, but we have to mention that).<br>
<br>
Thanks for showing an interest in Benevolent Order.  I look forward to meeting and playing with you all.<br>
<br>
One last task for you:  Reply to this message.  Nothing fancy, just something so we know that you have read and understand what is expected of you ).  This also gives us an idea of who has accomplished their first task of registering and creating an account to access our message boards.<br>
<br>
Good luck and Welcome to Benevolent Order,<br>
<br>
Brastil Shadowhunter<br>
Recruiting Officer<br>
